<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Services</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 20px;
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .logo {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .logo img {
      max-width: 200px;
    }

    nav ul {
      list-style-type: none;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    nav ul li {
      display: inline;
      margin-right: 20px;
    }

    nav ul li a {
      text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 18px;
      transition: color 0.3s;
    }

    nav ul li a:hover {
      color: #095a02;
    }

    #services {
      text-align: center;
    }

    #services h2 {
      color: #095a02;
      font-size: 32px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .services-container {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      justify-content: center;
    }

    .service {
      width: 300px;
      margin: 20px;
      padding: 20px;
      border: 1px solid #ccc;
      border-radius: 5px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .service img {
      max-width: 150px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .service h3 {
      color: #095a02;
      font-size: 24px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .service p {
      font-size: 14px;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <header>
    <div class="logo">
      <img src="hms.jpg" alt="Hospital Logo">
    </div>
    <nav>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/">Home Page</a></li>
        <li><a href="/services">Services</a></li>
        <li><a href="/doctor">Doctors</a></li>
        <li><a href="/Register">Registration</a></li>
        <li><a href="/appointment">Appointments</a></li>
        <li><a href="/contact">Contact</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
  </header>
  <section id="services">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Our Services</h2>
      <div class="services-container">
        <div class="service">
          <img src="consultn.jpeg" alt="Service 1">
          <h3>Medical Consultation</h3>
          <p>A medical consultation is a professional interaction between a patient and a healthcare provider, such as a doctor, where the patient discusses their health concerns and the provider assesses their condition. The provider gathers information about the patient's symptoms, medical history, and conducts any necessary examinations or tests.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service">
          <img src="service.jpeg" alt="Service 2">
          <h3>Diagnostic Tests</h3>
          <p>Diagnostic tests are medical procedures or examinations conducted to identify, detect, or confirm the presence of a disease, condition, or specific health markers in an individual. These tests are performed using various techniques, such as laboratory analysis of blood, urine, or tissue samples, imaging scans like X-rays, CT scans, or MRIs, and specialized procedures like biopsies or endoscopies.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service">
          <img src="service2.jpeg" alt="Service 3">
          <h3>Surgical Procedures</h3>
          <p>Surgical procedures are medical interventions that involve the use of instruments and techniques to address or treat a specific medical condition through invasive methods. These procedures are typically performed by trained surgeons in a sterile operating room environment.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service">
          <img src="physical.jpeg" alt="Service 4">
          <h3>Physical Therapy</h3>
          <p>Physical therapy, also known as physiotherapy, is a healthcare profession that focuses on improving physical function, mobility, and quality of life for individuals with injuries, illnesses, or disabilities. It involves the assessment, diagnosis, and treatment of musculoskeletal, neurological, and cardiopulmonary conditions through therapeutic exercises, manual techniques, and modalities.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service">
          <img src="radio.jpeg" alt="Service 5">
          <h3>Radiology Services</h3>
          <p>Radiology services are a crucial component of medical diagnostics and imaging. It is a branch of medicine that uses various imaging technologies to visualize and examine the internal structures of the body. Radiology plays a vital role in diagnosing and monitoring diseases or injuries, guiding treatment decisions, and evaluating the effectiveness of interventions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service">
          <img src="emergency.jpeg" alt="Service 6">
          <h3>Emergency Care</h3>
          <p>Emergency care, also known as emergency medicine, is a specialized branch of medical care that focuses on the prompt assessment, treatment, and stabilization of acute injuries and illnesses. It is provided in emergency departments or trauma centers and is designed to address critical and life-threatening conditions that require immediate medical attention. Emergency care involves a multidisciplinary team of healthcare professionals, including emergency physicians, nurses, paramedics, and other specialists.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</body>

</html>
